    <text id="B0085T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Garrett's letter to Jordan deals with discrepancies between the wages owed to
                    several men, and the obligations their employer (name unclear) assumed for
                them.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Office Va. Central <abbr expan="Railroad">R. R.</abbr> Company
                    <name type="recipient"><abbr expan="Colonel">Col.</abbr> Jno W.
                        Jordan<lb/>Staunton</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1868-05-08">May 8, 1868</date>
                        <name type="place">Richmond</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>Yours of this date is received. Mr. <unclear>Chunnery</unclear> the <unclear>new</unclear>
                    <del rend="none" hand="h1"/>
                    <unclear>Muster</unclear> notified me a short time ago not to pay any of the men
                    employed on his <del rend="none" hand="h1"/> as he had assumed obligations for many of them
                    which were to be paid out of their wages. I therefore refer you to him and if
                    you will obtain from Mr. F. J. <unclear>Chunnery</unclear> a statement showing
                    the <abbr expan="amount">amt.</abbr> due William Meredith after deducting such
                    obligations (if any have been incurred on his account) I will pay the amount
                    found to be due. The payroll for April has not been received at this office
                    &amp; I do not know what is due <abbr expan="William">Wm.</abbr> Meredith
                    for that month.</p>

                <p>The amounts appearing due on payrolls for January, <abbr expan="February"
                    >Feb'y</abbr> &amp; March are:<lb/> January 14.30<lb/> February 14.20<lb/>
                    March 21.15<lb/> April Not Known--<lb/> (Subject to deductions (if any) for
                    obligations incurred by <unclear>Ch-g</unclear> as above mentioned) </p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours Respectfully</salute>
                    <signed>J. Garrett, Jr.</signed>
                    <seg type="postscript">P.S. I return Meredith's order
                    herewith.<lb/>J.G.Jr.</seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
